From 2b0dbb9f07161eca3a82a91dda07eba78f5c2b07 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci7lus <7887955+ci7lus@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 18:55:36 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 9025/9025] demux/mpeg: Retry ProbeEnd when tail probing hits
 premature EOF

HTTP TS streams can report a Content-Length that includes trailing padding
or otherwise exceeds the actual TS payload size. In that case ProbeEnd may
seek close to the real end, ProbeChunk may read only a few packets, and EOF
can arrive before a full probe chunk is consumed.

The previous code aborted the backward search as soon as ProbeChunk
returned a partial chunk after having read more than one packet. A handful
of tail packets is rarely enough to contain a PCR, so ProbeEnd can fail
even though a valid PCR exists slightly further back.

Treat any short read as a sign that the reported size overshot the real end
of content and continue backing up by another probe chunk until a PCR is
found or PROBE_MAX is exhausted.
---
 modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c | 16 ++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c b/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
index 7b7b461f6eb..beda877ef04 100644
--- a/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
+++ b/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
@@ -2269,10 +2269,18 @@ int ProbeEnd( demux_t *p_demux, int i_program )
 
         int i_count = ProbeChunk( p_demux, i_program, true, &b_found );
         if( i_count < PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT )
-            break;
-
-        /* Go ahead one more chunk if end of file contained only stuffing packets */
-        i_probe_count += i_count;
+        {
+            /* Reported stream size can exceed the actual TS payload size.
+             * When the backward probe lands near the real end of content,
+             * ProbeChunk may hit EOF before reading a full chunk. Retry from
+             * a further-back position before giving up. */
+            i_probe_count += PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT;
+        }
+        else
+        {
+            /* Go ahead one more chunk if end of file contained only stuffing packets */
+            i_probe_count += i_count;
+        }
     } while( i_pos > 0 && !b_found &&
              i_probe_count < PROBE_MAX );
 
